In anaerobic digestion, retention time is defined as the average time spent by the substrate inside the digester before it comes out after the action of microorganisms in the bioreactor. Retention time is one the key factors that controls the extent to which volatile solids in the substrate are converted to biogas. In typical continuous stirred-tank anaerobic digestion systems the solids retention time (SRT) is equal to the hydraulic retention time (HRT). HRT is directly related to reactor volume, by the equation:HRT = (V)/(Q),\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
